msgstr "2. Meditation "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 13. Sekkhasutta → sekho (pts1)
msgctxt "sn45.13:0.3"
msgid "13. Sekkhasutta "
msgstr "13. A Trainee "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn45.13:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn45.13:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha … and asked him, "

msgctxt "sn45.13:1.3"
msgid "“‘sekkho, sekkho’ti, bhante, vuccati. "
msgstr "“Sir, they speak of this person called ‘a trainee’. "

msgctxt "sn45.13:1.4"
msgid "Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, sekkho hotī”ti? "
msgstr "How is a trainee defined?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn45.13:2.1"
msgid "“Idha, bhikkhu, sekkhāya sammādiṭṭhiyā samannāgato hoti … pe … sekkhena sammāsamādhinā samannāgato hoti. "
msgstr "“Mendicant, it’s someone who has a trainee’s right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. "

msgctxt "sn45.13:2.2"
msgid "Ettāvatā kho, bhikkhu, sekkho hotī”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how a trainee is defined.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn45.13:2.3"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

